ty through strategic purchasing we are able to offer the latest in branded clothing shoes accessories baby products and home furnishings at great savings bring your talents and ambition to one of the most exciting retailers in america and watch your career take off we are a strong and growing brand revenues exceeding  billion in  operates  stateoftheart distribution centers across the us publically traded on the nyse burl offprice retail is one of the fastest growing market segments burlington corporate stores distribution centers collegeinternships buying  planning about us company overview our burlington rewards social responsibility investor relations pressmedia room other shop with us new stores search jobs seasonal jobs privacy policy site map burlington corporate stores distribution centers collegeinternships buying  planning about us company overview our burlington rewards social responsibility investor relations pressmedia room other shop with us new stores search jobs seasonal jobs privacy policy site map burlington stores inc is an equal opportunity employer committed to a diverse and inclusive work environment   burlington stores all rights reserved burlington stores inc burlk company profile  reuterscom x edition united states africa américa latina عربي argentina brasil canada  deutschland españa france india italia  méxico россия united kingdom united states profile burlington stores inc burlk related topics stocksstock screenerdiscount stores overview news key developments people charts financials analysts research pulse burlk on new york consolidated usd  jul  change  chg   prev close  open  days high  days low  volume  avg vol  wk high  wk low  full description burlington stores inc incorporated on february   is a retailer of branded apparel as of january   the company operated  retail stores inclusive of an internet store in  states and puerto rico its product categories include coats women men juniors girls boys shoes handbags and accessories beauty and fragrance home and toys the product categories for coats include womens coats and jackets mens coats and jackets juniors coats and jackets girls coats and jackets boys coats and jackets baby girl coats and jackets and baby boy coats and jackets the product categories for women include active wear bottoms coats and jackets dresses tops scrubs suit and suit separates sweaters swimwear and coverups it also includes accessories beauty and fragrance handbags jewelry shoes and watches the product categories for men include accessories active wear casual button down shirts dress shirts mens coats jackets fleece graphic tees hoodies and sweatshirts jeans joggers long sleeve pajamas and robes pants polos shorts socks and underwear suits and suit separates sweaters vests and swimwearthe product categories for juniors include bottoms coats and jackets dresses jumpsuits and rompers sweaters swimwear and tops the product categories for girls include active wear backpacks and luggage bottoms capris cardigans and shrugs character tees girls coats and jackets communion dresses girls accessories hoodies and sweatshirts jeans joggers leggings girls sets shirts and blouses shorts skirts girls sleepwear socks and underwear special occasion sweaters and swimwear the product categories for boys include boys sets boys school uniforms button down shirts casual sets character tees boys coats and jackets dress wear dress wear sets dress pants dress shirts hoodies and sweatshirts jeans joggers polo shirts shorts and sleepwear the womens shoes that the company offers include boots booties comfort flats pumps and heels rain boots sandals and flip flops sneakers and wedges mens shoes include boat boots dress sneakers and wedges kids shoes include baby shoes toddlers shoes girl shoes and boys shoes the handbags and accessories include backpacks clutches cross body designer hobos leather satchels totes and wallets jewelry and watches it also offers other accessories including exercise hosiery slippers and sunglasses the beauty and fragrance products include perfume cologne make up bath and body and makeup bagsthe companys product offering for home category include bedding and bath furniture home decor kitchen and dining luggage rugs storage and organization window treatments and hardware home decor includes accent furniture wall art window treatments rugs lighting throw pillows blankets and throws storage furniture mirrors decorative bins and baskets clocks frames and candles and scents the product offering for kitchen and dining include appliances bake ware coffee and tea cookware cutlery food storage linens storage tools and gadgets trash cans bar and wine dinnerware drink ware flat ware and serve ware the company also offers toys » full overview of burlk company address burlington stores inc  route  northflorence   nj    p f  company web links home page officers  directors name compensation thomas kingsbury  marc katz  janet dhillon  joyce magrini  rick seeger  » more officers  directors burlington stores inc news briefintesa sanpaolo says burlington loan management to buy  pct of prelios jul   briefburlington stores inc reports q eps of  may   briefburlington stores reports q earnings per share  mar   briefpreit signs burlington as lead tenant to replace sears at magnolia mall feb   burlington to drop ivanka trump brand online business insider feb   » more burlk news related topics stocksstock screenerdiscount stores burlington department store  wikipedia burlington department store from wikipedia the free encyclopedia   redirected from burlington coat factory jump to navigation search not affiliated with burlington industries burlington stores inc type public traded as nyse burl industry retail founded   years ago  founders monroe milstein headquarters florence new jersey us number of locations   key people tom kingsbury president  ceo products clothes baby clothes furniture home decor items and gifts revenue us  billion  owner bain capital number of employees  website burlingtoncoatfactorycom burlington coat factory now known as burlington is an american national off price department store retailer and a division of burlington coat factory warehouse corporation with  stores in  states and puerto rico with its corporate headquarters located in burlington township new jersey in  it was acquired by bain capital in a takeprivate transaction and in  tom kingsbury became president and ceo the company went public again in  contents  history  charitable partnerships  business issues  references  external links historyedit the company was formed and incorporated in  when henrietta milstein convinced her husband monroe to purchase a former factory outlet in burlington new jersey for  using money she had saved from her job as a librarian for most of the  down payment monroe and his father abe milstein had been running a successful wholesale and retail outerwear business together since  initially the milsteins sold coats and jackets wholesale but in order to become less dependent on the seasonal coat business they gradually began adding additional clothing items and accessories eventually expanding into linens gift items a baby department and shoes a second location was opened in  in copiague on long island and milstein asked his son lazer who was living in israel at the time to return home and act the stores legal owner for the new location lazer agreed on the condition that the store be closed saturdays in observance of the sabbath at the time businesses faced legal action for being open on sunday with an exception made for religions observing a different sabbath in  with  locations the company whose name was burlington coat factory warehouse corporation since it was bought by the family in  went public in  the company was purchased by bain capital partners for  billion the milstein family held almost  million shares of the burlington coat factory warehouse corporation making approximately  billion and monroe milstein was unassociated with the business following the sale although two of his sons stephen and andrew stayed on briefly mark nesci the former executive vice president and chief operating officer was named to serve as the acting ceo a holding company called burlington coat factory holdings inc was formed to be the ultimate parent of the chain in july  the company received a  million incentive from the new jersey economic development authority as part of the states grownj program in order to build a new headquarters in florence adjacent to its existing headquarters keeping the company from moving its headquarters outside the state on june   burlington filed its s registration statement with the sec for an initial public offering in october  the companys stock rose more than  on its first day of trading the company reported  billion in sales for the month period ending august   as of october  the company operated  stores in  states and puerto rico under the names burlington coat factory cohoes fashions baby depot mjm designer shoes and burlington shoes in june  it was announced that burlington stores had joined the fortune  for the first time charitable partnershipsedit burlington has partnered with charitable organizations for several years since  they have partnered with the joining the leukemia and lymphoma society’s light the night campaign collecting donations at the store checkout with an annual fundraiser that runs from july through october the company raised more than  million in  bringing the total raised by the company to date to more than  million in  burlington launched the warm coats and warm hearts drive to collect coat donations for those in need partnering with abcs good morning america and the national nonprofit fashion delivers burlington stores served as drop off spots for the donations which were then distributed within the area by local charities since the programs inception over  million coats have been collected and distributed in  the company first partnered with womenheart the national coalition for women with heart disease to promote women’s heart health education during national heart health month as part of this partnership the company holds a yearly red dress event where red dresses are sold in stores with  from every sale donated to womenheart in  as part of the partnership they launched the “heart of style tour” for the tour a bus traveled to various store locations with heart health professionals on board providing blood pressure tests and body mass index bmi tests and education about womens heart disease business issuesedit under investigation from animal welfare organization humane society of the united states burlington coat factory has been accused of labeling real fur products as faux fur the company agreed to pull the false advertisements after an undercover investigation revealed faux fur as actually made from the pelts of animals killed in china burlington coat factorys coats have also been found to contain dog pelts from  until  burlington coat factorys logo was supplemented with the tag not affiliated with burlington industries when burlington coat factory settled a trademark dispute with fabric maker burlington industries in  burlington coat factory agreed to say in advertising that the two companies are not affiliated even though burlington industries ceased operations in  following a buyout of its remaining operations the not affiliated disclaimer remained on advertising logo and company media until  when the text was retired from all logos used by the company the old burlington coat factory on  park place in new york for many years after the september   attacks it was planned to be replaced by the unrelated controversial park a story residential tower is now planned instead in the september   attacks after hijacked united airlines flight  penetrated through the south tower of the world trade center part of the planes landing gear and fuselage came out the north side of the tower and crashed through the roof and two of the floors of the burlington coat factory at – park place between west broadway and church street  feet  meters north of the former world trade center the store had been the companys first location in manhattan opened in  three floor beams of the top floor of the building were destroyed causing major structural damage nearly nine years later the building was part of a national controversy as efforts to build a muslim center and mosque at the site as the cordoba house sparked protest referencesedit  a b burlington coat factory annual report k  pdf burlington  sec filings retrieved  may    a b bloomberg news  bain capital purchases burlington a retailer new york times retrieved    a b c strauss robert   billion later  nytimescom new york times retrieved    burlington coat factory offers range of rugs  free online library thefreelibrarycom  retrieved    apparel stores analysis monroe milstein  burlington coat factory warehouse corporation bcf  round table  shxtse twstcom retrieved    burlington stores inc  company profile from hoovers   webadepthooverscom  retrieved    twists quirks and coats success was based on family luck  and a crucial rule  phillycom articlesphillycom  retrieved    burlington coat factory corporate office  corporate offices  headquarters corporateofficehqcom retrieved    milsteins biggest deal burlington coat sold for  billion  phillycom articlesphillycom  retrieved    anne dinnocenzio burlington stores shares climb in market debut the reporter retrieved    michael mancuso  burlington coat factory receives m from grownj program to keep headquarters in new jersey njcom retrieved    burlington holdings inc form s received   nasdaqcom retrieved    pfeifer stuart  burlington coat factory ipo a big hit with investors latimescom retrieved    bain capitalbacked burlington stores sets terms for  million ipo nasdaqcom retrieved    burlington expects  million from ipo  mrketplace  mr magazine mrketplacecom  retrieved    avik