 became president and ceo the company went public again in  contents  history  charitable partnerships  business issues  references  external links historyedit the company was formed and incorporated in  when henrietta milstein convinced her husband monroe to purchase a former factory outlet in burlington new jersey for  using money she had saved from her job as a librarian for most of the  down payment monroe and his father abe milstein had been running a successful wholesale and retail outerwear business together since  initially the milsteins sold coats and jackets wholesale but in order to become less dependent on the seasonal coat business they gradually began adding additional clothing items and accessories eventually expanding into linens gift items a baby department and shoes a second location was opened in  in copiague on long island and milstein asked his son lazer who was living in israel at the time to return home and act the stores legal owner for the new location lazer agreed on the condition that the store be closed saturdays in observance of the sabbath at the time businesses faced legal action for being open on sunday with an exception made for religions observing a different sabbath in  with  locations the company whose name was burlington coat factory warehouse corporation since it was bought by the family in  went public in  the company was purchased by bain capital partners for  billion the milstein family held almost  million shares of the burlington coat factory warehouse corporation making approximately  billion and monroe milstein was unassociated with the business following the sale although two of his sons stephen and andrew stayed on briefly mark nesci the former executive vice president and chief operating officer was named to serve as the acting ceo a holding company called burlington coat factory holdings inc was formed to be the ultimate parent of the chain in july  the company received a  million incentive from the new jersey economic development authority as part of the states grownj program in order to build a new headquarters in florence adjacent to its existing headquarters keeping the company from moving its headquarters outside the state on june   burlington filed its s registration statement with the sec for an initial public offering in october  the companys stock rose more than  on its first day of trading the company reported  billion in sales for the month period ending august   as of october  the company operated  stores in  states and puerto rico under the names burlington coat factory cohoes fashions baby depot mjm designer shoes and burlington shoes in june  it was announced that burlington stores had joined the fortune  for the first time charitable partnershipsedit burlington has partnered with charitable organizations for several years since  they have partnered with the joining the leukemia and lymphoma society’s light the night campaign collecting donations at the store checkout with an annual fundraiser that runs from july through october the company raised more than  million in  bringing the total raised by the company to date to more than  million in  burlington launched the warm coats and warm hearts drive to collect coat donations for those in need partnering with abcs good morning america and the national nonprofit fashion delivers burlington stores served as drop off spots for the donations which were then distributed within the area by local charities since the programs inception over  million coats have been collected and distributed in  the company first partnered with womenheart the national coalition for women with heart disease to promote women’s heart health education during national heart health month as part of this partnership the company holds a yearly red dress event where red dresses are sold in stores with  from every sale donated to womenheart in  as part of the partnership they launched the “heart of style tour” for the tour a bus traveled to various store locations with heart health professionals on board providing blood pressure tests and body mass index bmi tests and education about womens heart disease business issuesedit under investigation from animal welfare organization humane society of the united states burlington coat factory has been accused of labeling real fur products as faux fur the company agreed to pull the false advertisements after an undercover investigation revealed faux fur as actually made from the pelts of animals killed in china burlington coat factorys coats have also been found to contain dog pelts from  until  burlington coat factorys logo was supplemented with the tag not affiliated with burlington industries when burlington coat factory settled a trademark dispute with fabric maker burlington industries in  burlington coat factory agreed to say in advertising that the two companies are not affiliated even though burlington industries ceased operations in  following a buyout of its remaining operations the not affiliated disclaimer remained on advertising logo and company media until  when the text was retired from all logos used by the company the old burlington coat factory on  park place in new york for many years after the september   attacks it was planned to be replaced by the unrelated controversial park a story residential tower is now planned instead in the september   attacks after hijacked united airlines flight  penetrated through the south tower of the world trade center part of the planes landing gear and fuselage came out the north side of the tower and crashed through the roof and two of the floors of the burlington coat factory at – park place between west broadway and church street  feet  meters north of the former world trade center the store had been the companys first location in manhattan opened in  three floor beams of the top floor of the building were destroyed causing major structural damage nearly nine years later the building was part of a national controversy as efforts to build a muslim center and mosque at the site as the cordoba house sparked protest referencesedit  a b burlington coat factory annual report k  pdf burlington  sec filings retrieved  may    a b bloomberg news  bain capital purchases burlington a retailer new york times retrieved    a b c strauss robert   billion later  nytimescom new york times retrieved    burlington coat factory offers range of rugs  free online library thefreelibrarycom  retrieved    apparel stores analysis monroe milstein  burlington coat factory warehouse corporation bcf  round table  shxtse twstcom retrieved    burlington stores inc  company profile from hoovers   webadepthooverscom  retrieved    twists quirks and coats success was based on family luck  and a crucial rule  phillycom articlesphillycom  retrieved    burlington coat factory corporate office  corporate offices  headquarters corporateofficehqcom retrieved    milsteins biggest deal burlington coat sold for  billion  phillycom articlesphillycom  retrieved    anne dinnocenzio burlington stores shares climb in market debut the reporter retrieved    michael mancuso  burlington coat factory receives m from grownj program to keep headquarters in new jersey njcom retrieved    burlington holdings inc form s received   nasdaqcom retrieved    pfeifer stuart  burlington coat factory ipo a big hit with investors latimescom retrieved    bain capitalbacked burlington stores sets terms for  million ipo nasdaqcom retrieved    burlington expects  million from ipo  mrketplace  mr magazine mrketplacecom  retrieved    avik das  burlington stores returns to market shares jump  pct  chicago tribune articleschicagotribunecom retrieved    here are the  new companies joining the fortune  fortunecom  retrieved    burlington to raise funds for blood cancer research retailing today  retrieved    style files fashions that benefit light the night wgntv  retrieved    bonander ross  burlington coat factory raises  million for the lls lymphomainfo